-- Liverpool Coach Kenny Dalglish Nears Long-Term Contract: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2011-02-04T10:09:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-04/liverpool-coach-kenny-dalglish-nears-long-term-contract-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Dalglish’s Job  Liverpool is moving closer to making Kenny Dalglish
permanent coach, the  Daily Mail  reported.  Dalglish has made the atmosphere at Anfield “far more
relaxed and positive,” according to the Mail, which cited a
club source.  Reina Wants Out  Liverpool goalkeeper Pepe Reina may follow Spanish
compatriot Fernando Torres out of the club at the end of the
season,  Metro  reported.  Reina could move to  Manchester United , the newspaper
reported.  Beckham’s ‘Semi’  Tottenham coach  Harry Redknapp  said he may try to sign  David Beckham  in November, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Redknapp said the Los Angeles Galaxy midfielder impressed
him with his enthusiasm while training with the London team over
the last few weeks, according to the Mirror.  “I’m sure he has a decent enough semi in Los Angeles but
he’s over here wanting to play football,” Redknapp said.  Chelsea Clearout  Chelsea is planning a summer clearout that could see five
players including Didier Drogba and Florent Malouda leave
Stamford Bridge,  the Sun  reported.  There could be a few “notable casualties” after the Blues
spent 75 million pounds on  Fernando Torres  and David Luiz in the
transfer window, the Sun quoted a team source as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
